libbsdmalloc combines source code under two licenses. Each governs different
portions of the library, according to where that code originated:

  * BSD 3-Clause - code derived from FreeBSD's sys/sys/malloc.h. In
    include/sys/malloc.h these are the malloc()/free() declarations (with
    __malloc_like, __result_use_check and __alloc_size) and the M_ZERO
    zero-in-place malloc() macro together with its explanatory comment.
        Copyright (c) 1987, 1993 The Regents of the University of California.
        Copyright (c) 2005, 2009 Robert N. M. Watson.
        SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause

  * MIT - the remaining original code: the #include_next wrapper arrangement
    that lets this header stand in front of the kernel's own <sys/malloc.h>,
    the _MALLOC()/_FREE() re-declarations, the XNU compatibility guards for
    __malloc_like and __predict_true()/__predict_false(), and the wrapper
    definitions in malloc.c. (malloc.c parenthesises the function name to
    suppress the macro, an idiom used by FreeBSD's sys/kern/kern_malloc.c;
    the function bodies themselves are original.)
        Copyright (c) 2022-2026 Sunneva N. Mariu

Where original code is combined with, or is a modification of, the
FreeBSD-derived sources, the BSD 3-Clause terms apply to that code.


